12/07/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Croatian Foreign Minister Miomir Zuzul said Sunday (11 July) he expects Serbia's new president, Boris Tadic, to work towards strengthening bilateral ties. 
Zuzul, who attended the swearing-in ceremony, also praised Tadic's inauguration speech, saying it reflected a firm intention to follow the path of EU integration. 
The Croatian delegation met with Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic and top Serbian officials to discuss regional co-operation issues. 
(Vecernji List - 12/07/04; HINA - 11/07/04)
